-- 
Customers in Serbia Use 1 Million Smart Phones, Danas Reports

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-07-11T08:57:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/customers-in-serbia-use-1-million-smart-phones-danas-reports.html
The number of smart phones in  Serbia 
has reached 1 million, or just over 10 percent of 9.92 million
mobile phone users,  Danas  newspaper reported, citing the three
providers on the market.  With the greater use of smart phones, Internet access from
mobile devices almost doubled to 70,000 users last year from
37,000 in 2009, the newspaper said. The penetration rate in the
country of 7.5 million people was at 132.23 percent at the end
of 2010, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  